\fs30 \cf2 7\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 But the Israelites were unfaithful in regard to the devoted things
\f0\b\fs16 \super [a]
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub ;\'a0Achan\'a0son of Karmi, the son of Zimri,
\f0\b\fs16 \super [b]
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub \'a0the son of Zerah,\'a0of the tribe of Judah,\'a0took some of them. So the\'a0Lord\'92s anger burned\'a0against Israel.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Who acted unfaithfully?  It says Israel but who really did it?\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Just one man\'85this is important as we move forward.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf2 \super 2\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai,\'a0which is near Beth Aven\'a0to the east of Bethel,\'a0and told them, \'93Go up and spy out\'a0the region.\'94 So the men went up and spied out Ai.\

\f0\b\fs18 \super 3\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub When they returned to Joshua, they said, \'93Not all the army will have to go up against Ai. Send two or three thousand men to take it and do not weary the whole army, for only a few people live there.\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}As I said earlier, they just had this HUGE battle where God showed up in a big way.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}And the guy is telling them that it isn\'92t near what we just went through so just send a small army.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf2 \super 4\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub So about three thousand went up; but they were routed by the men of Ai,\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 5\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub who killed about thirty-six\'a0of them. They chased the Israelites from the city gate as far as the stone quarries and struck them down on the slopes. At this the hearts of the people melted in fear and became like water.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The first thing I want you to see in this passage is their view of God\'92s blessing\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We walk through life with this loser believer attitude about life.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I believe that none of us have a clue about how much God wants to bless our lives and what it really means to have God winds at our back\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf2 \super 6\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then Joshua tore his clothes\'a0and fell facedown\'a0to the ground before the ark of the\'a0Lord, remaining there till evening.\'a0The elders of Israel\'a0did the same, and sprinkled dust\'a0on their heads.\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 7\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And Joshua said, \'93Alas, Sovereign\'a0Lord, why\'a0did you ever bring this people across the Jordan to deliver us into the hands of the Amorites to destroy us?\'a0If only we had been content to stay on the other side of the Jordan!\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 8\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Pardon your servant, Lord. What can I say, now that Israel has been routed by its enemies?\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 9\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub The Canaanites and the other people of the country will hear about this and they will surround us and wipe out our name from the earth.\'a0What then will you do for your own great name?\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}He\'92s having a little mini melt down here.  \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}He\'92s being a little over dramatic for me but you know\'85\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}There was roughly 600,000 fighting men who crossed over the Jordan with Joshua and 36 died.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}.006% of your army died in one battle and now you\'92re all going to die!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Essentially though\'85he is scared and he runs first to God.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf4 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}When bad things happen\'85who do you run to first.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Let me put it this way\'85is God first or last to hear about your problems?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf2 \super 10\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub The\'a0Lord\'a0said to Joshua, \'93Stand up! What are you doing down on your face?\'a0Essentially God is telling Joshua to relax\'85chill out a little buddy\'85it isn\'92t nearly as bad as you are making it out to be.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You\'92re still alive aren\'92t you?  You still have breath right?  OK...we can fix this.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf2 \super 11\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Israel has sinned;\'a0they have violated my covenant,\'a0which I commanded them to keep. They \cf0 Hold up, this is important\'85who took the stuff?  Yeah, the one guy.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}And who is God blaming\'85them!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf2 have taken some of the devoted things; they have stolen, they have lied,\'a0they have put them with their own possessions. That is why\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Meaning in light of what I just said.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Meaning because of what was just spoken about\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Meaning there is a cause and effect process going on here\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf2 the Israelites cannot stand against their enemies;\'a0they turn their backs\'a0and run\'a0because they have been made liable to destruction.\'a0I will not be with you anymore\'a0unless you destroy whatever among you is devoted to destruction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}3 Things I want you to see here:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf4 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}With God \'96 the unrealistic become expected, without God the expected become unrealistic\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf4 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Sin will do three things in your life\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl1
\f1\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It will take you farther than you wanted to go\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It will keep you longer than you wanted to stay\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It will cost you more than you wanted to pay.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It will affect more than immediately involved\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1440\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf4 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The issue is Follow God, not being a good person\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl1
\f1\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Because there is a temptation to focus on the wrong thing we tend find this story disturbing!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This guy steals a little thing that is not affecting or hurting anyone else\'85and God starts killing people for it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf5 10 commandment illustration\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The issue is important not because of the natural consequences but because of the specific call.\
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl2\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God told them specifically what to and not to do.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf6 Transition:  It is hard to tell which person we are trying to become\'85\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0
\f1\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}If it\'92s to be good:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We will look at other people & rules as a judge of our condition\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We will work on external issues to appear better than we are and not get caught\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Our goal is to be a good person and not get caught\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is done through management of do\'92s and don\'92ts from a rulebook.  \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1800\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}If it\'92s to Follow:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls17\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We will look to what God is calling us to do specifically\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We will work on internal issues that no one sees, knowing it will eventually change the external that everyone sees.  \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The goal is to live out our unique calling\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is done through personal conversations, obedience to our call, and repentance in areas we fail.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf6 What this looks like in our own world:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It\'92s the sermon you heard and were convicted to do something and then by the time you got home you forgot or talked yourself out of it\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It\'92s the voice in your head during your quiet time that called you to give something up and you know you probably should but come on\'85it\'92s not hurting anyone!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The leading when talking with someone or siting by yourself to do something that makes no sense to you\'85but it just won\'92t go away.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It\'92s the thing you know you shouldn\'92t be doing and are convicted before and after but continue because you believe the lie\'85it\'92s not hurting anyone else.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf6 Transition:  They catch him and this is what he says\'85\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb100\sa100\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf2 \super 20\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Achan replied, \'93It is true! I have sinned against the\'a0Lord, the God of Israel. This is what I have done:\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 21\'a0
\f1\b0\fs24 \nosupersub When I saw in the plunder\'a0a beautiful robe from Babylonia,
